#. <section class="sutta" id="mn137"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn137:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 137"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 137"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn137:0.2"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "The Analysis of the Six Sense Fields"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn137:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn137:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn137:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn137:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn137:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:2.1"
msgid "“saḷāyatanavibhaṅgaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi."
msgstr "“Mendicants, I shall teach you the analysis of the six sense fields."

msgctxt "mn137:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn137:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn137:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.216"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: yoggācariyānaṃ → yogācariyānaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn137:3.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, cha bāhirāni āyatanāni "
"veditabbāni, cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā, cha phassakāyā veditabbā, aṭṭhārasa "
"manopavicārā veditabbā, chattiṃsa sattapadā veditabbā, tatra idaṃ nissāya "
"idaṃ pajahatha, tayo satipaṭṭhānā yadariyo sevati yadariyo sevamāno satthā "
"gaṇamanusāsitumarahati, so vuccati yoggācariyānaṃ anuttaro "
"purisadammasārathī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"“The six interior sense fields should be understood. The six exterior sense "
"fields should be understood. The six classes of consciousness should be "
"understood. The six classes of contact should be understood. The eighteen "
"mental neighborhoods should be understood. The thirty-six bases pertaining "
"to pleasure should be understood. Therein, relying on this, give up that. "
"The Noble One cultivates the establishment of mindfulness in three cases, by "
"virtue of which they are a Teacher worthy to instruct a group. Of all "
"meditation teachers, it is he that is called the supreme guide for those who "
"wish to train in training."

msgctxt "mn137:3.2"
msgid "ayamuddeso saḷāyatanavibhaṅgassa."
msgstr ""
"This is the recitation passage for the analysis of the six sense fields."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:4.1"
msgid "‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:4.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn137:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘Cakkhāyatanaṃ sotāyatanaṃ ghānāyatanaṃ jivhāyatanaṃ kāyāyatanaṃ manāyatanaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"There are the sense fields of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "mn137:4.4"
msgid "cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:4.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (1)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:5.1"
msgid "‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:5.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn137:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘Rūpāyatanaṃ saddāyatanaṃ gandhāyatanaṃ rasāyatanaṃ phoṭṭhabbāyatanaṃ "
"dhammāyatanaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"There are the sense fields of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and "
"thoughts."

msgctxt "mn137:5.4"
msgid "cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:5.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (2)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:6.1"
msgid "‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:6.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn137:6.3"
msgid ""
"‘Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ sotaviññāṇaṃ ghānaviññāṇaṃ jivhāviññāṇaṃ kāyaviññāṇaṃ "
"manoviññāṇaṃ—"
msgstr "There are eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind consciousness."

msgctxt "mn137:6.4"
msgid "cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:6.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (3)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:7.1"
msgid "‘Cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:7.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn137:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘Cakkhusamphasso sotasamphasso ghānasamphasso jivhāsamphasso kāyasamphasso "
"manosamphasso—"
msgstr "There is contact through the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "mn137:7.4"
msgid "cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:7.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (4)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.217"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:8.1"
msgid "‘Aṭṭhārasa manopavicārā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The eighteen mental neighborhoods should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:8.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn137:8.3"
msgid ""
"‘Cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā somanassaṭṭhānīyaṃ rūpaṃ upavicarati, "
"domanassaṭṭhānīyaṃ rūpaṃ upavicarati, upekkhāṭṭhānīyaṃ rūpaṃ upavicarati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing a sight with the eye, you linger in the neighborhood of a sight that’"
"s a basis for happiness or sadness or equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:8.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "Hearing a sound with the ear …"

msgctxt "mn137:8.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "Smelling an odor with the nose …"

msgctxt "mn137:8.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn137:8.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "Feeling a touch with the body …"

msgctxt "mn137:8.8"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya somanassaṭṭhānīyaṃ dhammaṃ upavicarati, "
"domanassaṭṭhānīyaṃ dhammaṃ upavicarati, upekkhāṭṭhānīyaṃ dhammaṃ upavicarati."
msgstr ""
"Becoming conscious of a thought with the mind, you linger in the "
"neighborhood of a phenomena that’s a basis for happiness or sadness or "
"equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:8.9"
msgid ""
"Iti cha somanassūpavicārā, cha domanassūpavicārā, cha upekkhūpavicārā, "
"aṭṭhārasa manopavicārā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"So there are six neighborhoods near happiness, six neighborhoods near "
"sadness, and six neighborhoods near equanimity. ‘The eighteen mental "
"neighborhoods should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:8.10"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (5)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:9.1"
msgid "‘Chattiṃsa sattapadā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The thirty-six bases pertaining to pleasure should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:9.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

#. VAR: gehasitāni → gehassitāni (?)
msgctxt "mn137:9.3"
msgid ""
"Cha gehasitāni somanassāni, cha nekkhammasitāni somanassāni, cha gehasitāni "
"domanassāni, cha nekkhammasitāni domanassāni, cha gehasitā upekkhā, cha "
"nekkhammasitā upekkhā."
msgstr ""
"There are six kinds of lay happiness and six kinds of renunciate happiness. "
"There are six kinds of lay sadness and six kinds of renunciate sadness. "
"There are six kinds of lay equanimity and six kinds of renunciate equanimity."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:10.1"
msgid "Tattha katamāni cha gehasitāni somanassāni?"
msgstr "And in this context what are the six kinds of lay happiness?"

msgctxt "mn137:10.2"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyānaṃ rūpānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ manoramānaṃ "
"lokāmisapaṭisaṃyuttānaṃ paṭilābhaṃ vā paṭilābhato samanupassato pubbe vā "
"paṭiladdhapubbaṃ atītaṃ niruddhaṃ vipariṇataṃ samanussarato uppajjati "
"somanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasing, connected with the world’s carnal delights. Happiness arises when "
"you regard it as a gain to obtain such sights, or when you recollect sights "
"you formerly obtained that have passed, ceased, and perished."

msgctxt "mn137:10.3"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati gehasitaṃ somanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such happiness is called lay happiness."

msgctxt "mn137:10.4"
msgid "Sotaviññeyyānaṃ saddānaṃ …"
msgstr "There are sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "mn137:10.5"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyānaṃ gandhānaṃ …"
msgstr "Smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "mn137:10.6"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyānaṃ rasānaṃ …"
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn137:10.7"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyānaṃ phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …"
msgstr "Touches known by the body …"

msgctxt "mn137:10.8"
msgid ""
"manoviññeyyānaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ … pe … somanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasing, "
"connected with the world’s carnal delights. Happiness arises when you regard "
"it as a gain to obtain such thoughts, or when you recollect thoughts you "
"formerly obtained that have passed, ceased, and perished."

msgctxt "mn137:10.9"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati gehasitaṃ somanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such happiness is called lay happiness."

msgctxt "mn137:10.10"
msgid "Imāni cha gehasitāni somanassāni."
msgstr "These are the six kinds of lay happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.218"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:11.1"
msgid "Tattha katamāni cha nekkhammasitāni somanassāni?"
msgstr "And in this context what are the six kinds of renunciate happiness?"

msgctxt "mn137:11.2"
msgid ""
"Rūpānaṃ tveva aniccataṃ viditvā vipariṇāmavirāganirodhaṃ, ‘pubbe ceva rūpā "
"etarahi ca sabbe te rūpā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato uppajjati somanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When you’ve understood the impermanence of sights—their perishing, fading "
"away, and cessation—happiness arises as you truly understand through right "
"understanding that both formerly and now all those sights are impermanent, "
"suffering, and perishable."

msgctxt "mn137:11.3"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasitaṃ somanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such happiness is called renunciate happiness."

msgctxt "mn137:11.4"
msgid "Saddānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "When you’ve understood the impermanence of sounds …"

msgctxt "mn137:11.5"
msgid "gandhānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "smells …"

msgctxt "mn137:11.6"
msgid "rasānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "tastes …"

msgctxt "mn137:11.7"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "touches …"

msgctxt "mn137:11.8"
msgid ""
"dhammānaṃ tveva aniccataṃ viditvā vipariṇāmavirāganirodhaṃ, ‘pubbe ceva "
"dhammā etarahi ca sabbe te dhammā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato uppajjati somanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"thoughts—their perishing, fading away, and cessation—happiness arises as you "
"truly understand through right understanding that both formerly and now all "
"those thoughts are impermanent, suffering, and perishable."

msgctxt "mn137:11.9"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasitaṃ somanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such happiness is called renunciate happiness."

msgctxt "mn137:11.10"
msgid "Imāni cha nekkhammasitāni somanassāni."
msgstr "These are the six kinds of renunciate happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:12.1"
msgid "Tattha katamāni cha gehasitāni domanassāni?"
msgstr "And in this context what are the six kinds of lay sadness?"

msgctxt "mn137:12.2"
msgid "Cakkhuviññeyyānaṃ rūpānaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasing, connected with the world’s carnal delights. Sadness arises when "
"you regard it as a loss to lose such sights, or when you recollect sights "
"you formerly lost that have passed, ceased, and perished."

msgctxt "mn137:12.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "Such sadness is called lay sadness."

msgctxt "mn137:12.4"
msgid "sotaviññeyyānaṃ saddānaṃ …"
msgstr "There are sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "mn137:12.5"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyānaṃ gandhānaṃ …"
msgstr "There are smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "mn137:12.6"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyānaṃ rasānaṃ …"
msgstr "There are tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn137:12.7"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyānaṃ phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …"
msgstr "There are touches known by the body …"

msgctxt "mn137:12.8"
msgid ""
"manoviññeyyānaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ manoramānaṃ "
"lokāmisapaṭisaṃyuttānaṃ appaṭilābhaṃ vā appaṭilābhato samanupassato pubbe vā "
"appaṭiladdhapubbaṃ atītaṃ niruddhaṃ vipariṇataṃ samanussarato uppajjati "
"domanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasing, connected with the world’s carnal delights. Sadness arises when "
"you regard it as a loss to lose such thoughts, or when you recollect "
"thoughts you formerly lost that have passed, ceased, and perished."

msgctxt "mn137:12.9"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ domanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati gehasitaṃ domanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such sadness is called lay sadness."

msgctxt "mn137:12.10"
msgid "Imāni cha gehasitāni domanassāni."
msgstr "These are the six kinds of lay sadness."

