#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.219"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:13.1"
msgid "“Tattha katamāni cha nekkhammasitāni domanassāni?"
msgstr "And in this context what are the six kinds of renunciate sadness?"

msgctxt "mn137:13.2"
msgid ""
"Rūpānaṃ tveva aniccataṃ viditvā vipariṇāmavirāganirodhaṃ, ‘pubbe ceva rūpā "
"etarahi ca sabbe te rūpā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anuttaresu vimokkhesu pihaṃ upaṭṭhāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"When you’ve understood the impermanence of sights—their perishing, fading "
"away, and cessation—you truly understand through right understanding that "
"both formerly and now all those sights are impermanent, suffering, and "
"perishable. Upon seeing this, you give rise to yearning for the supreme "
"liberations:"

#. VAR: kudāssu → kudassu (bj) | kadāssu (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn137:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ tadāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharissāmi yadariyā etarahi "
"āyatanaṃ upasampajja viharantī’ti iti anuttaresu vimokkhesu pihaṃ "
"upaṭṭhāpayato uppajjati pihapaccayā domanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, when will I enter and remain in the same dimension that the noble ones "
"enter and remain in today?’ When you give rise to yearning for the supreme "
"liberations like this, sadness arises because of the yearning."

msgctxt "mn137:13.4"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ domanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasitaṃ domanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such sadness is called renunciate sadness."

msgctxt "mn137:13.5"
msgid "Saddānaṃ tveva … pe …"
msgstr "When you’ve understood the impermanence of sounds …"

msgctxt "mn137:13.6"
msgid "gandhānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "smells …"

msgctxt "mn137:13.7"
msgid "rasānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "tastes …"

msgctxt "mn137:13.8"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "touches …"

msgctxt "mn137:13.9"
msgid ""
"dhammānaṃ tveva aniccataṃ viditvā vipariṇāmavirāganirodhaṃ, ‘pubbe ceva "
"dhammā etarahi ca sabbe te dhammā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anuttaresu vimokkhesu pihaṃ upaṭṭhāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"thoughts—their perishing, fading away, and cessation—you truly understand "
"through right understanding that both formerly and now all those thoughts "
"are impermanent, suffering, and perishable. Upon seeing this, you give rise "
"to yearning for the supreme liberations:"

msgctxt "mn137:13.10"
msgid ""
"‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ tadāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharissāmi yadariyā etarahi "
"āyatanaṃ upasampajja viharantī’ti iti anuttaresu vimokkhesu pihaṃ "
"upaṭṭhāpayato uppajjati pihapaccayā domanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, when will I enter and remain in the same dimension that the noble ones "
"enter and remain in today?’ When you give rise to yearning for the supreme "
"liberations like this, sadness arises because of the yearning."

msgctxt "mn137:13.11"
msgid "Yaṃ evarūpaṃ domanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasitaṃ domanassaṃ."
msgstr "Such sadness is called renunciate sadness."

msgctxt "mn137:13.12"
msgid "Imāni cha nekkhammasitāni domanassāni."
msgstr "These are the six kinds of renunciate sadness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:14.1"
msgid "Tattha katamā cha gehasitā upekkhā?"
msgstr "And in this context what are the six kinds of lay equanimity?"

#. VAR: bālassa mūḷhassa → mūḷhassa mandassa (mr)
#. VAR: sā → sāyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn137:14.2"
msgid ""
"Cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati upekkhā bālassa mūḷhassa puthujjanassa "
"anodhijinassa avipākajinassa anādīnavadassāvino assutavato puthujjanassa."
msgstr ""
"When seeing a sight with the eye, equanimity arises for the uneducated "
"ordinary person—a foolish ordinary person who has not overcome their "
"limitations and the results of deeds, and is blind to the drawbacks."

msgctxt "mn137:14.3"
msgid "Yā evarūpā upekkhā, rūpaṃ sā nātivattati."
msgstr "Such equanimity does not transcend the sight."

msgctxt "mn137:14.4"
msgid "Tasmā sā upekkhā ‘gehasitā’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why it’s called lay equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:14.5"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When hearing a sound with the ear …"

msgctxt "mn137:14.6"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When smelling an odor with the nose …"

msgctxt "mn137:14.7"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When tasting a flavor with the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn137:14.8"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When feeling a touch with the body …"

msgctxt "mn137:14.9"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati upekkhā bālassa mūḷhassa puthujjanassa "
"anodhijinassa avipākajinassa anādīnavadassāvino assutavato puthujjanassa."
msgstr ""
"When knowing a thought with the mind, equanimity arises for the uneducated "
"ordinary person—a foolish ordinary person who has not overcome their "
"limitations and the results of deeds, and is blind to the drawbacks."

msgctxt "mn137:14.10"
msgid "Yā evarūpā upekkhā, dhammaṃ sā nātivattati."
msgstr "Such equanimity does not transcend the thought."

msgctxt "mn137:14.11"
msgid "Tasmā sā upekkhā ‘gehasitā’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why it’s called lay equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:14.12"
msgid "Imā cha gehasitā upekkhā."
msgstr "These are the six kinds of lay equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:15.1"
msgid "Tattha katamā cha nekkhammasitā upekkhā?"
msgstr "And in this context what are the six kinds of renunciate equanimity?"

msgctxt "mn137:15.2"
msgid ""
"Rūpānaṃ tveva aniccataṃ viditvā vipariṇāmavirāganirodhaṃ, ‘pubbe ceva rūpā "
"etarahi ca sabbe te rūpā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato uppajjati upekkhā."
msgstr ""
"When you’ve understood the impermanence of sights—their perishing, fading "
"away, and cessation—equanimity arises as you truly understand through right "
"understanding that both formerly and now all those sights are impermanent, "
"suffering, and perishable."

msgctxt "mn137:15.3"
msgid "Yā evarūpā upekkhā, rūpaṃ sā ativattati."
msgstr "Such equanimity transcends the sight."

msgctxt "mn137:15.4"
msgid "Tasmā sā upekkhā ‘nekkhammasitā’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why it’s called renunciate equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:15.5"
msgid "Saddānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "When you’ve understood the impermanence of sounds …"

msgctxt "mn137:15.6"
msgid "gandhānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "smells …"

msgctxt "mn137:15.7"
msgid "rasānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "tastes …"

msgctxt "mn137:15.8"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbānaṃ tveva …"
msgstr "touches …"

msgctxt "mn137:15.9"
msgid ""
"dhammānaṃ tveva aniccataṃ viditvā vipariṇāmavirāganirodhaṃ, ‘pubbe ceva "
"dhammā etarahi ca sabbe te dhammā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato uppajjati upekkhā."
msgstr ""
"thoughts—their perishing, fading away, and cessation—equanimity arises as "
"you truly understand through right understanding that both formerly and now "
"all those thoughts are impermanent, suffering, and perishable."

msgctxt "mn137:15.10"
msgid "Yā evarūpā upekkhā, dhammaṃ sā ativattati."
msgstr "Such equanimity transcends the thought."

msgctxt "mn137:15.11"
msgid "Tasmā sā upekkhā ‘nekkhammasitā’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why it’s called renunciate equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:15.12"
msgid "Imā cha nekkhammasitā upekkhā."
msgstr "These are the six kinds of renunciate equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:15.13"
msgid "‘Chattiṃsa sattapadā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The thirty-six bases pertaining to pleasure should be understood.’"

msgctxt "mn137:15.14"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.220"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:16.1"
msgid "‘Tatra idaṃ nissāya idaṃ pajahathā’ti—"
msgstr "‘Therein, relying on this, give up that.’"

msgctxt "mn137:16.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ; Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn137:16.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāni cha nekkhammasitāni somanassāni tāni nissāya tāni "
"āgamma yāni cha gehasitāni somanassāni tāni pajahatha, tāni samatikkamatha."
msgstr ""
"Therein, by relying and depending on the six kinds of renunciate happiness, "
"give up and go beyond the six kinds of lay happiness."

msgctxt "mn137:16.4"
msgid "Evametesaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametesaṃ samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:16.5"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāni cha nekkhammasitāni domanassāni tāni nissāya tāni "
"āgamma yāni cha gehasitāni domanassāni tāni pajahatha, tāni samatikkamatha."
msgstr ""
"Therein, by relying on the six kinds of renunciate sadness, give up the six "
"kinds of lay sadness."

msgctxt "mn137:16.6"
msgid "Evametesaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametesaṃ samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:16.7"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yā cha nekkhammasitā upekkhā tā nissāya tā āgamma, yā cha "
"gehasitā upekkhā tā pajahatha tā samatikkamatha."
msgstr ""
"Therein, by relying on the six kinds of renunciate equanimity, give up the "
"six kinds of lay equanimity."

msgctxt "mn137:16.8"
msgid "Evametāsaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:16.9"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāni cha nekkhammasitāni somanassāni tāni nissāya tāni "
"āgamma yāni cha nekkhammasitāni domanassāni tāni pajahatha, tāni "
"samatikkamatha."
msgstr ""
"Therein, by relying on the six kinds of renunciate happiness, give up the "
"six kinds of renunciate sadness."

msgctxt "mn137:16.10"
msgid "Evametesaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametesaṃ samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:16.11"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yā cha nekkhammasitā upekkhā tā nissāya tā āgamma yāni cha "
"nekkhammasitāni somanassāni tāni pajahatha, tāni samatikkamatha."
msgstr ""
"Therein, by relying on the six kinds of renunciate equanimity, give up the "
"six kinds of renunciate happiness."

msgctxt "mn137:16.12"
msgid "Evametesaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametesaṃ samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:17.1"
msgid ""
"Atthi, bhikkhave, upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā, atthi upekkhā ekattā "
"ekattasitā."
msgstr ""
"There is equanimity that is diversified, based on diversity, and equanimity "
"that is unified, based on unity."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:18.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā?"
msgstr "And what is equanimity based on diversity?"

msgctxt "mn137:18.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi, bhikkhave, upekkhā rūpesu, atthi saddesu, atthi gandhesu, atthi "
"rasesu, atthi phoṭṭhabbesu—"
msgstr ""
"There is equanimity towards sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches."

msgctxt "mn137:18.3"
msgid "ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā."
msgstr "This is equanimity based on diversity."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:19.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā?"
msgstr "And what is equanimity based on unity?"

msgctxt "mn137:19.2"
msgid ""
"Atthi, bhikkhave, upekkhā ākāsānañcāyatananissitā, atthi "
"viññāṇañcāyatananissitā, atthi ākiñcaññāyatananissitā, atthi "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatananissitā—"
msgstr ""
"There is equanimity based on the dimensions of infinite space, infinite "
"consciousness, nothingness, and neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn137:19.3"
msgid "ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā."
msgstr "This is equanimity based on unity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:20.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā taṃ nissāya taṃ āgamma "
"yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā taṃ pajahatha, taṃ samatikkamatha."
msgstr ""
"Therein, relying on equanimity based on unity, give up equanimity based on "
"diversity."

msgctxt "mn137:20.2"
msgid "Evametissā pahānaṃ hoti, evametissā samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how it is given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.221"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:20.3"
msgid ""
"Atammayataṃ, bhikkhave, nissāya atammayataṃ āgamma yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā "
"ekattasitā taṃ pajahatha, taṃ samatikkamatha."
msgstr "Relying on non-identification, give up equanimity based on unity."

msgctxt "mn137:20.4"
msgid "Evametissā pahānaṃ hoti, evametissā samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how it is given up."

msgctxt "mn137:20.5"
msgid "‘Tatra idaṃ nissāya idaṃ pajahathā’ti—"
msgstr "‘Therein, relying on this, give up that.’"

msgctxt "mn137:20.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:21.1"
msgid ""
"‘Tayo satipaṭṭhānā yadariyo sevati, yadariyo sevamāno satthā "
"gaṇamanusāsitumarahatī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The Noble One cultivates the establishment of mindfulness in three cases, "
"by virtue of which they are a Teacher worthy to instruct a group.’"

msgctxt "mn137:21.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;"
msgstr "That’s what I said,"

msgctxt "mn137:21.3"
msgid "kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "but why did he say it?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:22.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, satthā sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti anukampako hitesī anukampaṃ "
"upādāya:"
msgstr ""
"The first case is when the Teacher teaches the Dhamma out of kindness and "
"compassion:"

msgctxt "mn137:22.2"
msgid "‘idaṃ vo hitāya, idaṃ vo sukhāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘This is for your welfare. This is for your happiness.’"

msgctxt "mn137:22.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa sāvakā na sussūsanti, na sotaṃ odahanti, na aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapenti, "
"vokkamma ca satthusāsanā vattanti."
msgstr ""
"But their disciples don’t want to listen. They don’t pay attention or apply "
"their minds to understand. They proceed having turned away from the Teacher’"
"s instruction."

# The Burmese manuscripts appear to be alone in having “displeasure” here. Nor is it supported by the commentary, which has Na ca attamanoti na sakamano. (Sidebar: what? Is this normal in the comms? But at least it’s clearly not the negative form.) However, acc to Analayo, CSMN vol 2 p 786 note 145 the the Buremse agrees with the Chinese. Surely this makes more sense.
msgctxt "mn137:22.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgato na ceva anattamano hoti, na ca anattamanataṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti, anavassuto ca viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"In this case the Realized One is not displeased, he does not feel "
"displeasure. He remains unaffected, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "mn137:22.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ satipaṭṭhānaṃ yadariyo sevati, yadariyo sevamāno "
"satthā gaṇamanusāsitumarahati."
msgstr ""
"This is the first case in which the Noble One cultivates the establishment "
"of mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:23.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, satthā sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti anukampako hitesī "
"anukampaṃ upādāya:"
msgstr ""
"The next case is when the Teacher teaches the Dhamma out of kindness and "
"compassion:"

msgctxt "mn137:23.2"
msgid "‘idaṃ vo hitāya, idaṃ vo sukhāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘This is for your welfare. This is for your happiness.’"

msgctxt "mn137:23.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa ekacce sāvakā na sussūsanti, na sotaṃ odahanti, na aññā cittaṃ "
"upaṭṭhapenti, vokkamma ca satthusāsanā vattanti;"
msgstr ""
"And some of their disciples don’t want to listen. They don’t pay attention "
"or apply their minds to understand. They proceed having turned away from the "
"Teacher’s instruction."

msgctxt "mn137:23.4"
msgid ""
"ekacce sāvakā sussūsanti, sotaṃ odahanti, aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapenti, na ca "
"vokkamma satthusāsanā vattanti."
msgstr ""
"But some of their disciples do want to listen. They pay attention and apply "
"their minds to understand. They don’t proceed having turned away from the "
"Teacher’s instruction."

msgctxt "mn137:23.5"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgato na ceva anattamano hoti, na ca anattamanataṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti;"
msgstr "In this case the Realized One is not displeased,"

msgctxt "mn137:23.6"
msgid "na ca attamano hoti, na ca attamanataṃ paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr "nor is he pleased."

msgctxt "mn137:23.7"
msgid "Anattamanatā ca attamanatā ca—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn137:23.8"
msgid "tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"Rejecting both displeasure and pleasure, he remains equanimous, mindful and "
"aware."

msgctxt "mn137:23.9"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ satipaṭṭhānaṃ yadariyo sevati, yadariyo "
"sevamāno satthā gaṇamanusāsitumarahati."
msgstr ""
"This is the second case in which the Noble One cultivates the establishment "
"of mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.222"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:24.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, satthā sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti anukampako hitesī "
"anukampaṃ upādāya:"
msgstr ""
"The next case is when the Teacher teaches the Dhamma out of kindness and "
"compassion:"

msgctxt "mn137:24.2"
msgid "‘idaṃ vo hitāya, idaṃ vo sukhāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘This is for your welfare. This is for your happiness.’"

msgctxt "mn137:24.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa sāvakā sussūsanti, sotaṃ odahanti, aññācittaṃ upaṭṭhapenti, na ca "
"vokkamma satthusāsanā vattanti."
msgstr ""
"And their disciples want to listen. They pay attention and apply their minds "
"to understand. They don’t proceed having turned away from the Teacher’s "
"instruction."

msgctxt "mn137:24.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgato attamano ceva hoti, attamanatañca paṭisaṃvedeti, "
"anavassuto ca viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"In this case the Realized One is not pleased, he does not feel pleasure. He "
"remains unaffected, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "mn137:24.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ satipaṭṭhānaṃ yadariyo sevati, yadariyo "
"sevamāno satthā gaṇamanusāsitumarahati."
msgstr ""
"This is the third case in which the Noble One cultivates the establishment "
"of mindfulness."

msgctxt "mn137:24.6"
msgid ""
"‘Tayo satipaṭṭhānā yadariyo sevati, yadariyo sevamāno satthā "
"gaṇamanusāsitumarahatī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The Noble One cultivates the establishment of mindfulness in three cases, "
"by virtue of which they are a Teacher worthy to instruct a group.’"

msgctxt "mn137:24.7"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:25.1"
msgid "‘So vuccati yoggācariyānaṃ anuttaro purisadammasārathī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Of all meditation teachers, it is he that is called the supreme guide for "
"those who wish to train.’"

msgctxt "mn137:25.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

# It seems that the text is paralleling sārita with sārathi. They are, however from different roots: sārita is pp of the cause sareti, to make move, i.e. drive. Sārathi is sa-rathin, with chariot. It might be either a pun or a dialectical confusion.
msgctxt "mn137:25.3"
msgid "Hatthidamakena, bhikkhave, hatthidammo sārito ekaṃyeva disaṃ dhāvati—"
msgstr ""
"Driven by an elephant trainer, an elephant in training proceeds in just one "
"direction:"

msgctxt "mn137:25.4"
msgid "puratthimaṃ vā pacchimaṃ vā uttaraṃ vā dakkhiṇaṃ vā."
msgstr "east, west, north, or south."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:26.1"
msgid "Assadamakena, bhikkhave, assadammo sārito ekaññeva disaṃ dhāvati—"
msgstr ""
"Driven by a horse trainer, a horse in training proceeds in just one "
"direction:"

msgctxt "mn137:26.2"
msgid "puratthimaṃ vā pacchimaṃ vā uttaraṃ vā dakkhiṇaṃ vā."
msgstr "east, west, north, or south."

msgctxt "mn137:26.3"
msgid "Godamakena, bhikkhave, godammo sārito ekaññeva disaṃ dhāvati—"
msgstr ""
"Driven by an ox trainer, an ox in training proceeds in just one direction:"

msgctxt "mn137:26.4"
msgid "puratthimaṃ vā pacchimaṃ vā uttaraṃ vā dakkhiṇaṃ vā."
msgstr "east, west, north, or south."

msgctxt "mn137:26.5"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatena hi, bhikkhave, arahatā sammāsambuddhena purisadammo sārito aṭṭha "
"disā vidhāvati."
msgstr ""
"But driven by the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened "
"Buddha, a person in training proceeds in eight directions:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:27.1"
msgid "Rūpī rūpāni passati—"
msgstr "Having physical form, they see visions."

msgctxt "mn137:27.2"
msgid "ayaṃ ekā disā;"
msgstr "This is the first direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.3"
msgid "ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī bahiddhā rūpāni passati—"
msgstr "Not perceiving physical form internally, they see visions externally."

msgctxt "mn137:27.4"
msgid "ayaṃ dutiyā disā;"
msgstr "This is the second direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.5"
msgid "subhantveva adhimutto hoti—"
msgstr "They’re focused only on beauty."

msgctxt "mn137:27.6"
msgid "ayaṃ tatiyā disā;"
msgstr "This is the third direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.7"
msgid ""
"sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ "
"amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati—"
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of "
"impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is "
"infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "mn137:27.8"
msgid "ayaṃ catutthī disā;"
msgstr "This is the fourth direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.9"
msgid ""
"sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati—"
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space—aware that ‘"
"consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "mn137:27.10"
msgid "ayaṃ pañcamī disā;"
msgstr "This is the fifth direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.11"
msgid ""
"sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati—"
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘"
"there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"nothingness."

msgctxt "mn137:27.12"
msgid "ayaṃ chaṭṭhī disā;"
msgstr "This is the sixth direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.13"
msgid ""
"sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati—"
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in "
"the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn137:27.14"
msgid "ayaṃ sattamī disā;"
msgstr "This is the seventh direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.15"
msgid ""
"sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati—"
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, "
"they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "mn137:27.16"
msgid "ayaṃ aṭṭhamī disā."
msgstr "This is the eighth direction."

msgctxt "mn137:27.17"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatena, bhikkhave, arahatā sammāsambuddhena purisadammo sārito imā "
"aṭṭha disā vidhāvati."
msgstr ""
"Driven by the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, a "
"person in training proceeds in these eight directions."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:28.1"
msgid "So vuccati: ‘yoggācariyānaṃ anuttaro purisadammasārathī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Of all meditation teachers, it is he that is called the supreme guide for "
"those who wish to train.’"

msgctxt "mn137:28.2"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn137:28.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn137:28.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn137:28.5"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavibhaṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
